Investigate a Dateset Project

Egypt, Cairo

By Sherif Ahmed Abdelmagid Sakr

The FBI Gun Data Analysis Project as a part of Udacity Advanced Data Analyst Nanodegree Program is focus on analyze a dataset, use the Python libraries such as NumPy, pandas, Matplotlib, etc., and then communicate the findings about it, I apply the data analysis process which consists of asking questions, wrangling data (data gathering, data assessing, and data cleaning), exploring data analysis, draw conclusions, and communicate the findings.

The Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) is the domestic intelligence and security service of the United States of America, and its principal federal law enforcement agency. Operating under the jurisdiction of United States Department of Justice, the FBI is also a member of the U.S. Intelligence Community and reports to both the Attorney General and the Director of the National Intelligence.

Furthermore, FBI, the National Instant Criminal Backgroud Check System (NICS) is a background check system in the U.S. created by the Brady Handgun Violence Prevention Act, it short for Brady Act of 1993 to prevent firearm sales to people prohibited under the Act. The system was launched by the FBI in 1998.

Under the system, firearm dealers, gun shop owners, pawn shop dealer, retailer, manufactures, or importers who hold a Federal Firearms License (FFL) are required to undertakers a NICS background check on prospective buyers before transferring a firearm. However, NICS determine whether a person can legally buy or own a firearm. Operated by the FBI, NICS was developed with the Bureau of Alcohol, Tabacco, Firearms, and Explosives (ATF), and state, and law enforement agencies.

More details at:"https://www.fbi.gov/services/cjis/nics"

What will I learn? After completing the project, you will:

  • Know all the steps involved in a typical data analysis process

  • Be able to use vectorized operations in NumPy and Pandas to speed up your data analysis code
  • Be familiar with pandas' Series and DataFrame objects, which let you access your data more conveniently
  • Know how to use Matplotlib to produce plots showing your findings

Fist Step: Asking Question

Research Questions:

  • What is the total firearms registration in each U.S. States during the period from 1 November 1998 untill 1 September 2017?
  • What are the U.S. States with the highest number of the total firearms registration during the period from 1 November 1998 untill 1 September 2017?
  • What are the top ten U.S. States with the highest number of the total firearms registration during the period from 1 November 1998untill 1 September 2017?
  • What is the arithmetic mean (average) of the total firearms registration of each U.S. States during the period from 1 November 1998untill 1 September 2017?
  • Which U.S. States have the highest population in the 2016 census?
  • Which U.S. States have the highest population in the 2010 census?
  • What are the total payroll in each U.S. States over the 2015 year?
  • What are the total revenues of all firms in each of the U.S. States over the 2012 year?
  • What is the total firearms registration in each U.S. States over the 2017 year?
  • What is the highest number of total firearms registration over the U.S. States and over the 2017 year?
  • What is the lowest number of total firearms registration over the U.S. States and over the 2017 year?
  • What census data is most associated with the highest firearms registration per capita over the 2016 year?
  • Which U.S. States has the highest growth number of firearms registeration during the period from 1 November 1998 untill 1 September 2017?
  • What is the overall trend of firearms purchases?

Independent and Dependent Variables

  • In research, variables are any characteristics that can take on different values, such as height, temperature, age, species, or exam score. The variable in a study of a cause-and-effect relationship are called the independent and dependent variables.
  • The independent variable is the cause, its value is independent of other variables in the study. However, the dependent variable is the effect, its value depends on changes in the independent variable.
  • In other words, the independent variable is the variable the experimenter changes or controls and is assumed to have a direct effect on the dependent variable.
  • The research questions promote looking at relationships between multiple variables, and I aim to analyze at least one dependent variable and three independent variables in my investigation.
  • The dependent variable is the 'totals' column in the gun_data dataset representing the sum of all numerical columns of background checks data for each U.S. States.
  • The independent variables are all numerical variables in the U.S. census dataset.
  • Quantitative variables are any variables where the data represent amounts, and are numeric values that allows mathematical operations like most of the variables in this project (e.g. permits, totals 2010_population, and 2016_populations).
  • However, the categorical variables are any variables where the data represent groups. This includes rankings (e.g. finishing places in a race), classifications (e.g. brands of cereal), and binary outcomes (e.g. coin flips).

# Gathering Data

Load datasets to pandas Dataframe:

- A U.S. Census Data CSV file. It contains several variables at the state level. Most variables just have one data point per state.

- A NCIS Gun Data MS Excel file.It contains the number of firearm checks by month, state, and type.

- The datasets cover the period from November 1, 1998 untill September 1, 2017.

Note that, a comma-separate values (CSV) file is a delimited text file that use a comma to separate values.

  • Python has two kinds of loops: for loops and while loops.
  • A for loop is used to iterate, do something repeatedly, over an iterable.
  • An iterable is an object that can return on of its elements at a time. This can include sequence types, such as strings,lists
  • and tuples, as well as non-sequence types, such as dictionaries and files.
  • zip() and enumerate() are useful functions dealing with loops.
  • zip() function returns an iterator that combines multiple iterables into one sequence of tuples
  • enumerate() function returns an iterator of tuples containing indices and values of a list.

Limitations:

  • The datasets are separed into two tables.
  • The population estimates are covered only the 2010 and 2016 years.
  • There were missing values, NaN values, Null Values in both datasets.
  • There are five missing U.S. States (District of Columbia, Guam, Mariana Islands, Puerto Rico, and Virgin Island) in the U.S. census dataset, however, there are in the Gun dataset.
  • There are useless data in both datasets, and needed to be dropped.
  • The data in the Gun dataset cover the period from 1 November 1998 untill 1 September 2017, However, they were not updated to the present time.
  • The data types in the Gun dataset such as (permit, permit_recheck, handgun, long_gun, other, admin, prepawn_handgun, prepawn_long_gun, prepawn_other, redemption_handgun, redemption_long_gun, redemption_other, returned_handgun, returned_long_gun, returned_other, rentals_handgun, rentals_long_gun, private_sale_handgun, private_sale_other, return_to_seller_hand_gun, return_to_seller_long_gun,return_to_seller_other, and totals) were in float format and needed to converted into integer format for appropriate plotting the data).
  • the 'month' column which has a full date data in the Gun dataset was in string format and needed to convert to date format, and extract year and month in a separated columns for better analysis.
  • The comma which used to separate the numbers in the two datasets needed to be dropped for appropriate visualizing the data, and plotting them.
  • The dataset in the U.S. census needed to be transposed for appropiate analyzing and visualizing data.
  • The data in U.S. census dataset such as columns 'payroll_2015', 'revenue_2012', and 'employment_2015' which previously in rows before I transpoed the dataset and cover only 2015, 2012, and 2015 years, not the whole period.
  • The data in U.S. census dataset such as (Persons under 5 years, Persons under 18 years, Persons 65 years and over, Female persons, White, African American, Hawaiian, Hispanic, etc.) were in percentage rather than in numbers.
  • The column 'totals' in the Gun dataset as a result of mathematical operation is the sum of all previous columns such as (permit, permit_recheck, handgun, long_gun, other, admin, prepawn_handgun, prepawn_long_gun, prepawn_other, redemption_handgun, redemption_long_gun, redemption_other, returned_handgun, returned_long_gun, returned_other, rentals_handgun, rentals_long_gun, private_sale_handgun, private_sale_other, return_to_seller_hand_gun, return_to_seller_long_gun, and return_to_seller_other), however, some column such as (returned_handgun, returned_long_gun, returned_other,return_to_seller_long_gun, and return_to_seller_other) should had been subtracted from totals not added.

Overall Conclusion

  • The FBI Gun Data Analysis Project as a part of Udacity Advanced Data Analyst Nanodegree Program is focus on analyze a dataset, use the Python libraries such as NumPy, pandas, Matplotlib, etc., and then communicate the findings about it, I apply the data analysis process which consists of asking questions, wrangling data (data gathering, data assessing, and data cleaning), exploring data analysis, draw conclusions, and communicate the findings.

  • The FBI, the National Instant Criminal Backgroud Check System (NICS) is a background check system in the U.S. created by the Brady Handgun Violence Prevention Act, it short for Brady Act of 1993 to prevent firearm sales to people prohibited under the Act. The system was launched by the FBI in 1998.

  • However, The Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) is the domestic intelligence and security service of the United States of America, and its principal federal law enforcement agency. Operating under the jurisdiction of United States Department of Justice, the FBI is also a member of the U.S. Intelligence Community and reports to both the Attorney General, and the Director of the National Intelligence.

  • Under the system, firearm dealers, gun shop owners, pawn shop dealer, retailer, manufactures, or importers who hold a Federal Firearms License (FFL) are required to undertakers a NICS background check on prospective buyers before transferring a firearm. However, NICS determine whether a person can legally buy or own a firearm. Operated by the FBI, NICS was developed with the Bureau of Alcohol, Tabacco, Firearms, and Explosives (ATF), and state, and law enforement agencies.

  • The data in both Gun and U.S. census datasets are divided by the U.S. States.

  • According to the data analyzing and visualization phase, the overall trend of purchasing of different kinds of firearms are increasing rapidly.

  • In Statistics, probability distribution in graphics and plotting reveal the variables distribution: Normalized, right-skewed, or left-skewed. However, a correlation coefficient indicates the extent to which dots in the scatterplot lie on a straight line. This implies that we can usually estimate correlations pretty accurately from nothing more than scatterplot.

  • The formulas of correlation coefficient return a value between -1 and 1, where:

  • (+1) indicates the two variables have a strong positive relationship,the dots in a scatter plot lie exactly on a straight ascending line.
  • (-1) indicates the two variables have a strong negative relationship,and the data points in a scatter plot lie exactly on a straight descending line.

  • A correlation of zero indicates that the two variables have no relationship at all.

  • Most of numerical variables, quantitative variables as an independent variables have a positive relationships on the numerican variable, quantitative variable as dependent variable such as 'totals' variable. However, a Histograms and a scatterplotting indicate a positive linear relationships between indepdendent and dependent variables.

  • The U.S. census on both the 2010 and 2016 years reveal that the highest number of population on the State of California.

  • During the period of 1 November 1998 untill 1 September 2017, the U.S. State with the highest number of the total firearms registration is the Commonwealth of Kentucky State, however, the Mariana Islands, are an archipelago in the western North Pacific Ocean have the lowest number of the total firearms registration.
